               <p>JAMES BOND. I am servant to Mr. Richards, who lives in Union-street, Spitalfields. I saw the prisoner take the leg of mutton out of the shop about nine o'clock at night; I saw him lurking about the shop several times. I apprehended him, and took him into custody. I am sure he is the man. <rs id="t18170115-162-verdict879" type="verdictDescription">
